c-section.gloss: the delivery of a fetus by surgical incision through the abdominal wall and uterus (from the belief that Julius Caesar was born that way)

c. s. forester.gloss: English writer of adventure novels featuring Captain Horatio Hornblower (1899-1966)

cs.gloss: a soft silver-white ductile metallic element (liquid at normal temperatures)

cs gas.gloss: a tear gas that is stronger than CN gas but wears off faster

cse.gloss: Canadian agency that gathers communications intelligence and assist law enforcement and security agencies

csis.gloss: Canada's main foreign intelligence agency that gathers and analyzes information to provide security intelligence for the Canadian government

cst.gloss: standard time in the 6th time zone west of Greenwich, reckoned at the 90th meridian
